{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "chat_1",
      "provider": "chat",
      "name": "Chat",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "chat"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 20, "y": 200 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_rocketride_1",
      "provider": "agent_rocketride",
      "name": "Incident Diagnosis",
      "config": {
        "agent_description": "RescueOps++ on-call engineer that autonomously explores the Neo4j code graph via MCP, scores blast radius, retrieves runbooks, and returns a verified JSON diagnosis with a full-file candidate fix.",
        "instructions": [
          "You are an on-call engineer diagnosing a production incident in a TypeScript codebase.\nYou have access to a Neo4j code graph (Function, Test, Runbook nodes) via MCP tools, keyed memory across planning waves, and a Python tool to score blast radius.\n\n## Graph schema\n- (:Function) — properties: name, file, status (passing|failing|unknown), changed (boolean)\n- (:Test) — properties: name, file, status\n- (:Runbook) — properties: title, text\n- (:Function)-[:CALLS]->(:Function)\n- (:Test)-[:TESTS]->(:Function)\n- (:Runbook)-[:APPLIES_TO]->(:Function)\n\n## Investigation procedure (use waves efficiently)\n1. Wave 1: call neo4j.get-neo4j-schema, then read-cypher to find the root-cause Function (status='failing' or changed=true) and its file path.\n2. Wave 2: in parallel — (a) MATCH blast radius: `MATCH (root:Function {name: $name})-[:CALLS*0..3]-(down:Function) RETURN DISTINCT down.name, down.file, down.status`, (b) MATCH failing tests: `MATCH (t:Test)-[:TESTS]->(f:Function) WHERE f.status='failing' OR f.changed=true RETURN t.name, t.file`, (c) MATCH runbooks: `MATCH (rb:Runbook)-[:APPLIES_TO]->(f:Function {name: $name}) RETURN rb.title, rb.text`.\n3. Store findings in memory: root_cause, root_file, blast_radius, failing_tests, runbook_titles.\n4. Wave 3: use python.execute to score severity from blast radius. Pass a JSON string of {root_cause, blast_radius: [{name, status}], failing_test_count}. Example:\n```python\nimport json\npayload = json.loads('''PASTE_JSON_HERE''')\nblast = payload.get('blast_radius') or []\nfailing = int(payload.get('failing_test_count') or 0)\nchanged = sum(1 for n in blast if n.get('status') == 'failing')\nscore = min(100, 20 + len(blast) * 8 + failing * 12 + changed * 10)\nseverity = 'high' if score >= 60 else 'medium' if score >= 35 else 'low'\nprint(json.dumps({'severity_score': score, 'severity': severity, 'blast_count': len(blast)}))\n```\n5. Store severity result in memory.\n6. Final wave: synthesize diagnosis. Ground every claim in graph findings and any source snippets in the question. Quote the exact broken expression.\n\n## Output requirements\nRespond with ONLY a JSON object — no markdown fences, no prose — with exactly these keys:\n- severity: one of \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\" (use python scorer result when available)\n- root_cause_explanation: string\n- proposed_fix_approach: string (describe approach — do not write a diff)\n- cited_runbook: exact Runbook title from graph, or null\n- candidate_fix: object {path, content} — path is repo-relative (e.g. \"src/tax.ts\"), content is the FULL corrected source file verbatim with only the broken expression fixed\n\nIf the question requests N candidate variants, ALSO include candidate_fixes: array of N {path, content} objects; first must equal candidate_fix.\n\nPreserve every other line in candidate_fix.content exactly as in the provided source. Do not guess beyond graph + question context."
        ],
        "max_waves": 8,
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "input": [
        { "lane": "questions", "from": "chat_1" }
      ],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 280, "y": 200 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "memory_internal_1",
      "provider": "memory_internal",
      "name": "Memory (Internal)",
      "config": { "type": "memory_internal" },
      "control": [{ "classType": "memory", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 280, "y": 560 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_openai_api_1",
      "provider": "llm_openai_api",
      "name": "Butterbase AI Gateway",
      "config": {
        "profile": "custom",
        "custom": {
          "model": "${ROCKETRIDE_BUTTERBASE_MODEL}",
          "base_url": "${ROCKETRIDE_BUTTERBASE_GATEWAY_URL}",
          "modelTotalTokens": 32768,
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_BUTTERBASE_API_KEY}"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "control": [{ "classType": "llm", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 280, "y": 420 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "mcp_client_1",
      "provider": "mcp_client",
      "name": "Neo4j MCP",
      "config": {
        "type": "mcp_client",
        "serverName": "neo4j",
        "transport": "streamable-http",
        "http": {
          "endpoint": "${NEO4J_MCP_ENDPOINT}",
          "headers": {
            "Authorization": "Basic ${ROCKETRIDE_NEO4J_BASIC_AUTH}"
          }
        }
      },
      "control": [{ "classType": "tool", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 500, "y": 420 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_python_1",
      "provider": "tool_python",
      "name": "Blast Radius Scorer",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_python",
        "timeout": 30,
        "allowedModules": [
          { "moduleName": "json" },
          { "moduleName": "math" }
        ]
      },
      "control": [{ "classType": "tool", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 500, "y": 560 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "response_answers_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "name": "Return Answers",
      "config": { "laneName": "answers" },
      "input": [{ "lane": "answers", "from": "agent_rocketride_1" }],
      "ui": {
        "position": { "x": 700, "y": 200 },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    }
  ],
  "project_id": "efcc7864-f8b5-43df-9bac-860a84e6aac7",
  "viewport": { "x": 0, "y": 0, "zoom": 1 },
  "version": 1,
  "source": "chat_1"
